gomodel:SYNGO_2786  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Interaction between PSD-95 and Preso\"\n- \"These results suggest that PSD-95 promotes synaptic localization of Preso through their PDZ interaction.\"\n\nFig.2: \"Expression patterns of Preso mRNAs and proteins\"\n- \"Preso proteins were detected in various subcellular fractions of rat brain, including crude synaptosomes (P2), cytosol (S3), and light membranes (P3) (Fig. 2H). The upper, but not the lower, Preso band was enriched in postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions including the PSD III fraction (Fig. 2I), indicative of a very tight association with the PSD.\". Experimental description: - \"Cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 rat brain.\"\n- Overexpressed FRMPD4; preso is of human species: \"For Flag-tagged Preso expression constructs, the following regions of human Preso (KIAA0316) were subcloned into p3xFLAG-CMV7.1 (Sigma)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2786" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

